This dataset contains raw fMRI data for 22 healthy participants listening to an original audio narrative designed to elicit individual variation along an axis of suspicion/paranoia. For more details, please see the following publication:

Finn ES, Corlett PR, Chen G, Bandettini PA, Constable RT. "Trait paranoia shapes inter-subject synchrony in brain activity during an ambiguous social narrative." Nature Communications, 2018.

Preprint available here: https://www.biorxiv.org/content/early/2018/04/24/231738